    "content": "<p>Amino acid ' $X$ ' contains phenolic hydroxy group and amino acid ' $Y$ ' contains amide group. ' $X$ ' and ' $Y$ ' respectively are</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>Ser, Arg</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>Cys, Lys</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>Thr, Asn</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>Tyr, Gln</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The characteristic feature of given amino acids are</p>\n<p>$$ \\text { Ser } \\mathrm{HO}-\\mathrm{CH}_2- $$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TG EAPCET 2025 (Online) 4th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 11 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mjsu142f/03d65995-7468-4d7d-9fde-9d9491496e39/e6ce8e70-e5a0-11f0-8b28-a5a0a2cfc5cc/file-jaoe38c1mjsu142g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mjsu142f/03d65995-7468-4d7d-9fde-9d9491496e39/e6ce8e70-e5a0-11f0-8b28-a5a0a2cfc5cc/file-jaoe38c1mjsu142g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>Cys $\\mathrm{HS}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-$</p>\n<p>Lys $\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{~N}-\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_2\\right)_4-$</p>\n<p>Thr $\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CHOH}-$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TG EAPCET 2025 (Online) 4th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 11 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mjsu14lq/cf84cfa1-bace-4766-a4b1-06bd6c9fbd21/e7389ae0-e5a0-11f0-8b28-a5a0a2cfc5cc/file-jaoe38c1mjsu14lr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mjsu14lq/cf84cfa1-bace-4766-a4b1-06bd6c9fbd21/e7389ae0-e5a0-11f0-8b28-a5a0a2cfc5cc/file-jaoe38c1mjsu14lr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\text { Tyr } \\quad(p) \\mathrm{HO}-\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_4-\\mathrm{CH}_2- $$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TG EAPCET 2025 (Online) 4th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 11 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mjsu15ay/4a1ce1fa-03b5-46d2-89f5-68ee2f787ac7/e7c327a0-e5a0-11f0-8b28-a5a0a2cfc5cc/file-jaoe38c1mjsu15az.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mjsu15ay/4a1ce1fa-03b5-46d2-89f5-68ee2f787ac7/e7c327a0-e5a0-11f0-8b28-a5a0a2cfc5cc/file-jaoe38c1mjsu15az.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>Thus $X$ and $Y$ respectively are Tyr and Gln as they contain phenolic hydroxy group and amide group respectively.</p>",
