    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { The given general formula is } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mjlpv1u3/ee17fd42-1598-4e7f-bd45-572a82db9d95/1d2a6db0-e1b7-11f0-9c6e-0506fd1ead8a/file-jaoe38c1mjlpv1u4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mjlpv1u3/ee17fd42-1598-4e7f-bd45-572a82db9d95/1d2a6db0-e1b7-11f0-9c6e-0506fd1ead8a/file-jaoe38c1mjlpv1u4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2025 (Online) 4th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 12 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Then, $R=-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_4 \\mathrm{OH}$</p>\n<p>(para position) gives tyrosine.</p>\n<p>When $\\mathrm{R}=\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{SH} \\longrightarrow$ Cysteine</p>\n<p>When $R=\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CONH}_2 \\longrightarrow$</p>\n<p>Asparagine.</p>\n<p>When</p>\n<p>$$ R=-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{S}-\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\longrightarrow $$</p>\n<p>Methionine not serine.</p>\n<p>As serine has the $R$ group : $-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{OH}$</p>",
