    "content": "<p>Which of the following hormones is an example of polypeptide?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>Epinephrine</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>Insulin</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>Estrogen</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>Androgen</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct answer is:  </p>\n<p>✅ <strong>Option B: Insulin</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Polypeptide hormones</strong> are made up of chains of amino acids.  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Insulin</strong> is a classic example — it’s composed of two peptide chains (A and B chains) linked by disulfide bonds.  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Epinephrine</strong> is a <strong>catecholamine</strong> (derived from the amino acid tyrosine).  </p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Estrogen</strong> and <strong>androgen</strong> are <strong>steroid hormones</strong> derived from cholesterol.  </p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Hence, <strong>Insulin</strong> is the <strong>polypeptide hormone</strong> among the options.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "tg-eapcet-2025-online-2nd-may-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
