    "explanation": "<p>Statement $ I $ is incorrect but statement II is correct. The correct form of statement $ I $ is,</p>\n<p>Lactose commonly known as milk sugar is made up of $ \\beta $-D-galactose $ (A) $ and $ \\beta $-D-glucose $ (B) $.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m62id9m3/48366b18-ad1e-4e93-961a-ce21cc7ac40f/1a70cbb0-d5c8-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62id9m4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m62id9m3/48366b18-ad1e-4e93-961a-ce21cc7ac40f/1a70cbb0-d5c8-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62id9m4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 10th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 21 English Explanation\"></p>",
