      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Cellulose is a polysaccharide and it is made of $\\beta$-D glucose units joined through 1, 4-glycosidic linkage.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5qak0yx/39940ba3-a283-40f0-a42e-77c5851d7060/259a24a0-cf10-11ef-be11-e1052bd18398/file-jaoe38c1m5qak0yy.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5qak0yx/39940ba3-a283-40f0-a42e-77c5851d7060/259a24a0-cf10-11ef-be11-e1052bd18398/file-jaoe38c1m5qak0yy.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 9th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 23 English Explanation\">",
