  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "The functional groups involved in the conversion of glucose to gluconic acid and gluconic acid to saccharic acid respectively are",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5huw31j/e3d69edc-4307-4fc4-a7b1-235659ff8a35/9da68770-ca6c-11ef-a054-0b4b733aefe4/file-jaoe38c1m5huw31k.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5huw31j/e3d69edc-4307-4fc4-a7b1-235659ff8a35/9da68770-ca6c-11ef-a054-0b4b733aefe4/file-jaoe38c1m5huw31k.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 9th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 24 English Option 1\">"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$-\\mathrm{CHO},-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}_4-\\mathrm{CHO}$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5hv0t3l/1e1440c0-917f-448c-a41a-70b7ab663405/2103fc10-ca6d-11ef-a054-0b4b733aefe4/file-jaoe38c1m5hv0t3m.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5hv0t3l/1e1440c0-917f-448c-a41a-70b7ab663405/2103fc10-ca6d-11ef-a054-0b4b733aefe4/file-jaoe38c1m5hv0t3m.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 9th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 24 English Option 4\">"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "Glucose is converted to gluconic acid by oxidation with $\\mathrm{Br}_2$ water and to saccharic acid when oxidation is carried by conc. $\\mathrm{HNO}_3$. The reaction is as follows\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5i5o4ee/fb89e831-1cb5-48cf-8a3a-0d3603951c71/c4a57e60-ca96-11ef-aa80-ebe1872f5671/file-jaoe38c1m5i5o4ef.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5i5o4ee/fb89e831-1cb5-48cf-8a3a-0d3603951c71/c4a57e60-ca96-11ef-aa80-ebe1872f5671/file-jaoe38c1m5i5o4ef.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 9th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 24 English Explanation\">\nFunctional groups involved are -CHO and $-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$.",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2024-online-9th-may-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>From the following, the correct statements about polysaccharides are</p>\n<p>I. Starch is a polymer of $\\alpha-\\mathrm{D}(+)$-glucose.</p>\n<p>II. Amylose component of starch is not soluble in water.</p>\n<p>III. Amylose is a branched chain polymer of $\\alpha-\\mathrm{D}(+)$-glucose.</p>\n<p>IV. Cellulose is a straight chain polymer of $\\beta-\\mathrm{D}(+)$-glucose units.</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>I and IV only</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>II and III only</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>II and IV only</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>I and III only</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Starch is a condensation polymer of hundreds of $\\alpha-\\mathrm{D}(+)$-glucose monomer. Thus, statement I is correct.</p>\n<p>Amylose is solube in water and can be hydrolysed into glucose units by enzymes $\\alpha$-amylase. Amylase catalyses the hydrolysis of starch into sugar. So, statement (II) is incorrect. Amylose is an unbranched linear polymer composed of $\\alpha$-D-glucose units linked by $\\alpha-(1,4)$ linkages. So, statement (III) is incorrect.</p>\n<p>Cellulose is straight chain polymer compound of only D-glucose units joined by $\\beta$-glycosidic linkage. So, statement (IV) is correct.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2023-online-14th-may-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The deficiency of which vitamin causes pernicious anaemia?</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>Vitamin $B_2$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>Vitamin $\\mathrm{B}_6$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>Vitamin E</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>Vitamin $B_{12}$</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Deficiency of vitamin $B_{12}$ causes pernicious anaemia. (A decrease in red blood cells).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2023-online-14th-may-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A vitamin $X$ is soluble in fat and its source is egg yolk. Deficiency of $X$ causes the disease</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>scurvy</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>convulsions</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>xerophthalmia</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>rickets</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Vitamin D is soluble in fat and its sources are egg yolk, exposure to sunlight, fish etc. Deficiency of vitamin D causes rickets disease.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2023-online-13th-may-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>$$ \\text { The Haworth projection shown below represents } $$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2023 (Online) 13th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 10 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mkfgl0hp/33340309-b149-43e3-9435-367bd12c1ba9/575b26d0-f212-11f0-aa7a-bbc1e273ac26/file-jaoe38c1mkfgl0hq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mkfgl0hp/33340309-b149-43e3-9435-367bd12c1ba9/575b26d0-f212-11f0-aa7a-bbc1e273ac26/file-jaoe38c1mkfgl0hq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>",
    "options": [
