      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The given Haworth's projection is of $\\alpha$-D-(+) glucopyranose.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2023 (Online) 13th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 10 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mkfgkyxg/7f3fc493-f1a4-4194-95a2-094c87288bf2/56262940-f212-11f0-aa7a-bbc1e273ac26/file-jaoe38c1mkfgkyxh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mkfgkyxg/7f3fc493-f1a4-4194-95a2-094c87288bf2/56262940-f212-11f0-aa7a-bbc1e273ac26/file-jaoe38c1mkfgkyxh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>It has 6-membered pyranose ring having 5 -carbon atoms and one oxygen-atom. It is alpha because at $\\mathrm{C}-1$ atom, -OH group is present downwards.</p>",
    "topic": null,
