  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Assertion (A) In aqueous solution, amino acids exist in dipolar ion form.</p>\n<p>Reason (R) Most of the naturally occurring amino acids have $L$-configuration.</p>\n<p>The correct option among the following is</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true, (R) is true and (R) is the correct explanation for (A).</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true, (R) is true but (R) is not the correct explanation for (A).</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true but (R) is false.</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>(A) is false but (R) is true.</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Both (A) and (R) are true but (R) is not correct explanation for (A), as the amino acids exist in dipolar form due to presence of positive $\\left(-\\stackrel{+}{\\mathrm{N}} \\mathrm{H}_3\\right)$ group and negative ( $-\\mathrm{COO}^{-}$) group. The dipolar form is called as Zwitter ion form.</p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 20th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 3 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mnksz7xh/5e807d30-f867-4794-9c79-7a5d46125c63/615d1150-3067-11f1-8a57-016aede6d28f/file-jaoe38c1mnksz7xi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mnksz7xh/5e807d30-f867-4794-9c79-7a5d46125c63/615d1150-3067-11f1-8a57-016aede6d28f/file-jaoe38c1mnksz7xi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\">",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2022-online-20th-july-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>$$ \\text { Consider the following structures } $$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 2 English 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mng6206b/e69da09e-f42b-4def-ae6b-de339319fd5b/9a3b8b30-2dda-11f1-b97b-bd6d58bcbf9a/file-jaoe38c1mng6206c.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mng6206b/e69da09e-f42b-4def-ae6b-de339319fd5b/9a3b8b30-2dda-11f1-b97b-bd6d58bcbf9a/file-jaoe38c1mng6206c.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 2 English 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mng6215k/9ee8bb2d-fb1c-4f81-a14f-dd9ea8cbebe6/9afd2d80-2dda-11f1-b97b-bd6d58bcbf9a/file-jaoe38c1mng6215l.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mng6215k/9ee8bb2d-fb1c-4f81-a14f-dd9ea8cbebe6/9afd2d80-2dda-11f1-b97b-bd6d58bcbf9a/file-jaoe38c1mng6215l.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>Which of the pairs represent $D$ and $L$-fructose, respectively?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>II and I</p>\n"
      },
