  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Assertion (A) Both glucose and fructose have the same $D$-configuration.</p>\n<p>Reason (R) Both glucose and fructose are dextrorotatory.</p>\n<p>The correct option among the following is</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true, (R) is true and (R) is the correct explanation for (A)</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true, (R) is true but (R) is not the correct explanation for (A)</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true but (R) is false</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>(A) is false but (R) is true</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 4 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmx2lpmw/94ecf8ce-cad4-491f-9c6c-670a6f2b68ca/356b2880-235a-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2lpmx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmx2lpmw/94ecf8ce-cad4-491f-9c6c-670a6f2b68ca/356b2880-235a-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2lpmx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p><p>$D$ and $L$ configurations are relative configurations. Glucose and fructose</p><p></p>\n<p>both have -OH group on the bottom carbon to the right side. They have same $D$-configuration. Hence, they are called $D$-glucose and $D$-fructose. So, assertion (A) is true. Glucose rotates plane polarised light to the right side or clockwise direction. So, it is dextrorotatory.</p>\n<p>Whereas fructose rotates plane polarised light to left side or anti-clockwise. So, fructose is laevorotatory. So, given reason (R) is false.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2022-online-19th-july-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The amount of sucrose needed to produce 1 mole of glucose using acid hydrolysis is</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>360 g</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>180 g</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>342 g</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>171 g</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>1 mole of sucrose on acid hydrolysis produces 1 mole of glucose and 1 mole of fructose.</p>\n<p>$$ \\underset{\\text { Sucrose }}{\\mathrm{C}_{12} \\mathrm{H}_{22} \\mathrm{O}_{11}} \\xrightarrow{\\text { Acid hydrolysis }} \\underset{\\text { Glucose }}{\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_{12} \\mathrm{O}_6}+\\underset{\\text { Fructose }}{\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_{12} \\mathrm{O}_6} $$</p>\n<p>Molecular mass of sucrose</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} & =(12 \\times \\text { atomic mass of } \\mathrm{C})+(22 \\times \\text { mass of } \\\\ & \\mathrm{H})+(11 \\times \\text { Atomic mass of } \\mathrm{O}) \\\\ & =(12 \\times 12)+(22 \\times 1)+(11 \\times 16)=342 \\mathrm{~g} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Therefore, amount of sucrose needed to produce 1 mole of glucose using acid hydrolysis is 342 g .</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2022-online-18th-july-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Assertion (A) The denaturation of proteins can destroy all $1^{\\circ}, 2^{\\circ}$ and $3^{\\circ}$ protein structures.</p>\n<p>Reason (R) Curdling of milk is due to denaturation of proteins.</p>\n<p>The correct option among the following is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true, (R) is true and (R) is the correct explanation for (A)</p>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true, (R) is true but (R) is not the correct explanation for (A)</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>(A) is true but (R) is false</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>(A) is false but (R) is true</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The structure of proteins is destroyed by the application of heat or chemical agents and the process i. called denaturation. It involves the disruption of both the secondary and tertiary structures of a protein, but the primary structure, which involves a sequence of amino acids does not get disturbed and remains intact. This results in the loss of the biological activity of the proteins.</p>\n<p>The protein in milk is normally suspended in a colloidal solution, which means that the small protein molecules float around freely and independently. On adding lime juice to milk the pH decreases and the small protein molecules gets coagulated and forms large chain. This is denaturing of protein and causes curdling.</p>\n<p>Therefore the (A) is false but (R) is true.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2022-online-18th-july-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
